# Applying:
## Earth
-> Earth has near-earth-asteroids, or NEAs, and has hence not cleared its path. 
-> Some of these NEAs have their own satellites, about 104 of them. 
-> Earth also has a few other Trojans. 
-> Earth does not directly orbit the Sun since the Moon causes Earth to revolve around the Earth-Moon system's center of gravity. Though 
few scientists call this a 'wobble', these are small revolutions done by Earth not around the Sun. 
Therefore Earth must be called a dwarf-planet.
## Mars 
-> Mars too has near Mars Trojans that demote it from Planetary Status. 
## Jupiter
-> Jupiter has the highest number of Trojans. 
-> More than 1 million of these Trojans are larger than 1 km. 
-> This means that the second biggest object in the solar system is not a 'planet'. 
## Uranus and Neptune
-> They too have Trojans. 

 Venus, Saturn and some-how Mercury have clear orbits, but Venus and Saturn have 'temporary' trojans that we can consider, making these three the only true planets in the 
solar system. Unless we consider the fact that Mercury might be a ploonet, or that the Sun plays a major role in clearing the orbit, Mercury is the only true planet in 
the Solar System, followed by Venus and Saturn despite the presence of temporary trojans. 
